The CA-10 is built with a carbon-wrapped, match-grade barrel and is tipped with a titanium flash-hider or muzzle-brake. title: For Sale:  Black Powder Frame Colt .44-40  Etched Panel Frontier Six Shooter Revolver - 1882
postcontent:
Maker: Colt 

Model: Single Action Army Frontier Six Shooter 

Serial Number: 80378 

Year of Manufacture: 1882 

Caliber: .44 WCF 

Action Type: Single Action Revolver 

Markings: The left side of the barrel is etched “Colt Frontier Six Shooter”. The left side of the frame is marked “Pat. Sept. 19, 1871 / " July 2,-72 / " Jan. 19,-75”. The top of the barrel is marked “Colt’s Pt. F.A. Mfg. Co. Hartford, CT. U.S.A.”. The underside of the frame, back strap and trigger guard are marked “80378”. The loading gate is assembly numbered "5200". There is a "Ca" on the left forward trigger guard bow. 

Barrel Length: 7 ½’ 

Sights / Optics: The front sight is a fixed blade. The rear sight is a notched top strap. 

Stock Configuration & Condition: The grips are one piece smooth wood. The fit is very good, though just a bit shy. There is scattered marking and the finish is a dark oil. There is general wear at the edges and a possible light sanding. There are no splits. The grips rate in about Good overall condition. 

Type of Finish: Nickel 

Finish Originality: Original 

Bore Condition: The bore is gray and the rifling is present but worn. There is mild and even erosion in the bore. 

Overall Condition: This handgun retains about 3% of its metal finish. There are only traces of the original plating, though enough to determine it is a nickel gun. The balance of the gun is void of finish and drifting to a light patina. There is mild erosion throughout and some mottled aging. There are some tooling marks on the hammer, and someone has replaced the base pin screw, apparently it required being re-drilled and tapped. The gun has a great frontier appearance. The screw heads are worn but serviceable. The markings are light. Overall, this handgun rates in about Good condition. 

Mechanics: The action functions properly, though the lock up is not always strong. We did not fire this handgun. 

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: None 

Our Assessment: The Colt Frontier or Frontier Six-Shooter was a Colt's 1873 "Model P" type revolver, manufactured in .44-40 Winchester caliber instead of .45 Colt (in which configuration it was called the Single Action Army), so as to be cross-compatible with Winchester 1873 ammunition. Production began 1877. Colt Frontier Six-Shooter was the actual name of the Colt pistol model and this was acid-etched on the left side of the barrel. After 1889, the legend was roll-stamped until 1919. This is a desirable gun with the etched panel, and though there has been some metal work and wear, the gun remains acceptable.

postcontent: Here's a rather nice Colt Single Action Army revolver that was made just before the turn of the century. Chambered for the .44-40 cartridge, this is correctly rollmarked "Colt Frontier Six Shooter" on the left side of the 7-1/2" barrel. This original revolver retains lots of original finish. There are strong case colors remaining, particularly on the forward parts of the frame and hammer. The barrel and cylinder retain most of their original finish with some normal wear/thinning. An excellent revolver!

title: For Sale/Trade:  SIG 556 & Extras, Trade for Jeep
postcontent:
Im going to throw this out there see if there is any interest. I do love to barter 

I recently bought a .308 SCAR and just never shoot the SIG 556 enough to justify keeping it. First off im looking to trade everything pictured for a decent running Jeep to fix up and be a DD. Otherwise im asking $2600 for everything listed/pictured.

All I ask: Nothing rotted out, nothing beat to absolute ****, must have a title.Trade must be value for value. IE: A $500 Jeep would not be a trade for my offer. Just like my offer would not be a trade for a $5K Jeep. I can throw in some cash if we are a little ways apart. I paid well over $4000 for everything listed.
